      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FOXY TWO GLOVES (9) was out of the money two runs back at this track then improved sharply last start to score by 6 metres over 1790m at the same circuit. Draws out a little on the second line and may need luck at some point. Her last-start form is good enough to win a race of this calibre. THE NAKED ART (3) had a favourable gate and was too good at this track two runs ago. Drew a wide gate last start and was safely held, beaten 13 metres into fourth at this track over 2190m. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a similar line up and she is capable of a much better performance. GOOD BOOTS BINDI (1) was responsible for a better effort last time out when runner-up over 1790m at this track. Should run a big race. GO AWAY AGAIN (5) is worth some thought after his last-start fourth when resuming from a spell over 1790m at this track on February 25.",
